https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/

Analysis Source code : https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/sources_v4/
  gets you https://data.giss.nasa.gov/gistemp/sources_v4/gistemp4.0.tar.gz

What I need : f77 SOurce Code
mkdir F77
cd F77
wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/README.txt
wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/mkTsMap.f
wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/SBBX_to_nc.f
wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/SBBX_to_1x1.f
wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/SBBX_to_txt.f

What I need : data
mkdir DATA
cd DATA

1: SBBX.Tsurf1200  (44 MB) surf air temp (1880-present) 1200km smoothing
2: SBBX.Tsurf250   (19 MB) surf air temp (1880-present)  250km smoothing
3d: SBBX.ERSSTv5    (35 MB) sea surf temp. data (1880-present) - currently used

wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/SBBX1880.Ts.GHCNv4.1200.gz
wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/SBBX1880.Ts.GHCNv4.250.gz
wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/SBBX.ERSSTv5.gz

wget https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/gistemp1200_GHCNv4_ERSSTv5.zarr.tar.gz <<<<<<<<<< MOST IMPORTANT
[sergio@taki-usr2 DATA]$ gunzip gistemp1200_GHCNv4_ERSSTv5.zarr.tar.gz
[sergio@taki-usr2 DATA]$ tar -xvf gistemp1200_GHCNv4_ERSSTv5.zarr.tar
[sergio@taki-usr2 DATA]$ cd gistemp1200_GHCNv4_ERSSTv5.zarr


%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%%

now compile F77 code for primetime
see https://data.giss.nasa.gov/pub/gistemp/README.txt

+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++
+ The new conversion-to-netcdf program                              + 
+ ------------------------------------                              +
+ The following script produced the available netcdf files:         +
+                                                                   +    
+ ln SBBX.ERSSTv5 ERSST_DATA                                        +
+ ln SBBX1880.Ts.GHCN.CL.PA.1200 TS1200_DATA                        +
+ ln SBBX1880.Ts.GHCN.CL.PA.250  TS250_DATA                         +
+ gfortran -fconvert=big-endian SBBX_to_ncint.f -o SBBX_to_nc.exe \ +
+          -L/usr/lib64 -lnetcdf -lnetcdff -I/usr/include           +
+ ./SBBX_to_nc.exe 1200 5 1880 2016 9 gistemp1200_ERSST.nc          +
+ ./SBBX_to_nc.exe  250 0 1880 2016 9 gistemp250.nc                 +
+                                                                   +  
+ The arguments are in order:                                       +
+ smoothing radius            250 or 1200                           +
+ ocean index                 1=Hadley/Reynolds 3=ERSST 4=ERSSTv4   +
+ first year of series        1880 or later             5=ERSSTv5   +
+ last year month of series                                         +
+ name of output file                                               +
+                                                                   + 
+ Any other parameter changes have to be made in SBBX_to_ncint.f    +
+++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++++

so for us
cd F77

 ln -s ../DATA/SBBX1880.Ts.GHCNv4.250 TS250_DATA
 ln -s ../DATA/SBBX1880.Ts.GHCNv4.1200 TS1200_DATA
 #ln -s ../DATA/SBBX.ERSSTv5 ERSST_DATA                                        
 ln -s ../DATA/SBBX.ERSSTv5 ERSSTv5_DATA

 gfortran -fconvert=big-endian SBBX_to_nc.f -o SBBX_to_nc.exe -L/usr/lib64 -lnetcdf -lnetcdff -I/usr/include 
    oops has an error

  [sergio@taki-usr2 F77]$ nf-config --fc
  ifort

  ifort -convert big_endian SBBX_to_nc.f -o SBBX_to_nc.exe -L/usr/lib64 -lnetcdf -lnetcdff -I/usr/include
  ifort  -check bounds -g -traceback -debug inline-debug-info -check all -fp-stack-check -convert big_endian SBBX_to_nc.f -o SBBX_to_nc.exe -L/usr/lib64 -lnetcdf -lnetcdff -I/usr/include

 ./SBBX_to_nc.exe 1200 5 2002 2022 12 gistemp1200_ERSST.nc          
 ./SBBX_to_nc.exe  250 5 2002 2022 12 gistemp250_ERSST.nc

